The paper focuses on analyzing names in source code, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of topic modeling to analyze the names suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of Locality Sensitive Hashing, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with large datasets of repositories, which could fall under the category of databases (cs.DB).
